name: Brian Koppelman
bio: Co-creator/Showrunner/screenwriter/producer of Billions. Rounders, Ocean's Thirteen, Solitary Man, host of podcast The Moment.

social_posts.post_text: Screenwriting lesson disguised as a song.

One of the best fiction writers working in the English language. Every story in this book slays. The novel Netherland is a marvel, a dream, a perfection. This book is filled w little, also perfect things. It’s literature. But it’ll meet you wherever you are. @josephoneillwriter

Morning Pages (freehand writing first thing in the morning) are the cure for creative laryngitis. They give you back your most powerful, purist and truest voice. Always grateful to @juliacameronlive for putting this idea in the world and to @davidlevien for giving me The Artist’s Way 26 years ago.
It’s a hard game to get decent at.

This human spends her life celebrating other people. Today, we celebrate her. Simply the smartest, kindest, deepest person I’ve ever met. A great artist (she’d never call herself that despite writing the three acclaimed books and making the two films) with a completely original vision, a mom who’s raised two good people, a wife and partner who inspires me every day and has for the last 31 years. Happy Birthday, @amy_koppelman ! (She’s kinda pretty, too). I love you so much.

@emmawhitemusic has a song out right now called “Only Girl In This Town” that @steele_fountain and I wrote w her. I love this track. And I am always blown away by the way Emma refuses to let anyone else define her place in the world, in music, in the business. We’ve written a bunch together, and I always come away impressed anew. She knows exactly who she is as an artist. Go stream this on Spotify or Apple. Add to playlists. Dive in.
Game Theory w @bomani_jones!This Friday. Bo is a good friend, a great thinker, a helluva host w a strong POV. Plus, he sent me a mug! Watch the show. And enjoy your morning coffee, #theroyale

So fun to have cowritten a song on @spotify Country Fresh Finds playlist. @emmawhitemusic and Haley Steele (@steele_fountain) are so talented. It was a joy to ride along w them writing this. Go listen to Only Girl In This Town.  Also @greylanjames is really good. Good company to be in.

My brother @briankoppelman (he’s so great!) is my guest on the 100th episode of my Just Jenny podcast. Please listen and share with your people. Brian is a successful writer, tv maker, movie maker and podcaster, but to me, he’s just my big brother. Link in stories and in bio.

If you know me, you know that @slaidc’s songs are an obsession of mine. If I have 5 favorite songwriters, he’s one of them. And he and I wrote one together that’s on this record. I sent him a song. He said he thought he could tighten it up. Lemme tell ya, it’s tighter than a new lacrosse webbing now.  Go to Slaid’s insta to order the cd now. Or March 1 it’ll be on all the services. Truly an honor. And the album kicks ass. (Our song is second track on the album, Puncher’s Chance). The record is already #4 on the americana charts. Get yours now.

This album is an incredible collection of songs. Slaid has long been among my favorite artists. Way before I ever met him. When I write story songs, his songs are what I measure em against. Thank you, @slaidc for recording our song and putting it w this incredible grouping of songs. Love.
Cramer is incorrigible. Credit to a tiktoker called groovy_007 I think.

@bertkreischer’s life story, his career, his whole approach is remarkable. He says he’s a marketer. He’s an artist. And today this brilliant dude is on my podcast The Moment. Go listen. Prepare to be surprised. Also: he cries!! I firestoned him.
Love  to Nashville.

Sometimes things you see on the internet aren’t great in real life. But the spicy mashed, onion, chili hot dog from @chris_redhots is the tastiest hot dog I’ve ever eaten. We had the truck out to the Billions set tonight so we could all sample it. Get Tony and his truck out to a party or set soon. Or go visit him at his regular location. What a dog!
Um pretty big day for the ol’ podcast. Look for this is two weeks.
Value writers.
We need to make some changes. But all of em should focus on building around Jalen. #knicks
@stephen.wilson.jr is no joke. Proud to be his friend.
@sushinonakanyc is absolutely in a flow state. The food, service, vibe are perfect. Highly recommend.
Perfect morning w @amy_koppelman and some very kind friends who lured me to nature. Not my natural habitat. And yet.

From the moment I first read this novel, Signature Kill, 9 or 10 years ago, I thought it was the most accurate and compelling look into a serial killer’s mind and life I’d ever come across. And the similarities to the Gilgo Beach Killer are stunning. No one knows better than I do how deep David is willing to go to get it right as a writer. He never takes short cuts when it comes to research, depth of thought, craft. This novel is stylish, super intense, gripping but also important. If you missed it when it came out, fix that now. @davidlevien

Gut-punched about Sinead. The Lion and Cobra is one of my favorite albums of all time. I was at the SNL and the Dylan show. Saw all of it. Didn’t know her as a person. But loved her as an artist. Felt deeply for her. And wished she had peace in her life.

Her memoir is disturbing but important. And makes this, if not understandable, at least comprehensible when taken with the death of her son.

She was one of the greatest musical artists of my lifetime, if we judge by the apex of an artist’s creative output.

I will listen to the first two albums tonight, quietly, and I will try to just lose myself in them and in her artistic vision and hopes for the world.
My last favorite band. And long time friends. So glad to be with them tonight before they take the stage at @positivejamfest ! @theholdsteady !!! @steadycraig @tadkubler
Love you, Pop. Wish you were here to have seen this. You’d have gotten a kick out of it.
Always thought these made the round more fun. Glad to find the box.
Um Billions.
Kindness of strangers deserves grid post.

I’ve Loved These Days. Episode 709 of Billions is everything I love about getting to make this show w our incredible cast and my partner @davidlevien and our partner these last few years in this and Super Pumped, @bethshax and our longtime brother and collaborator @harrop634 who has been here with us since Solitary Man. The great Ben Shenkman has also shown up so huge for us for so long. And we waiting so long before finding the exact scene and moment to salute @billyjoel’s new york.  @shazbennett is another person who has been in our life for over 20 years, and she brought her whole self to this thing as a director. I’ll make an entire post about @marneemeyer soon enough over these last episodes but, in truth, in many ways, she’s as responsible for what billions feels like as any other individual who’s worked with us on the show. A genius editor. Go watch. Drink it in. I’ve Loved These Days.

He was 4 when we started going to knick games together. In about a month he turns 28. PrettttyGood. Go Knicks.
The Moment w Brian Koppelman. This week’s guest, Michael Lewis. Pls listen.

Michael Lewis and I really had a grown up and intensely engaged conversation about con artists, storytellers, perception, footnotes, and the value of close reading. If you ever listen to podcasts, pick this one today. The Moment w Brian Koppelman, wherever you pod.

What an honor and joy to be standing next to this guy in photos since the summer of 82. If there’s a smarter, more creative, more loyal person, I ain’t met them yet. Plus, he gets the references and never says “no one talks like that.” Cause he does, too. Hope yall dig the #Billions finale.
Omigod my sisters on Shark Tank!!! @bunnyeyez !!!

It’s a real dad and daughter night at @kingsbklyn for @lizphairofficial and @blondshell w my girl, @annarosekoppelman !! We have been listening to both artists since their first album (I mean, ya know, birthdates being what they are).
Push pull legs repeat.
Just a little more. The PR is 135 for two reps. The goal is 225 on the day I turn 60, in 2026.
Listen to the world around you. Find your stories.
